HEADWORD: critical point
<hw>crit"ic*al point</hw> <fld>(Physics)</fld>, <def>That combination of
volume and pressure, at the critical temperature of the substance, at
which the liquid and gaseous phases of a given quantity of a substance
have identical values for their densities and other
properties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>critical temperature</ent>⟦br⟧
